(1, 'Sakura Bath House', 100, 'Japan', 'Romance', 'The sakura bath house is a way to destress and have an intimate time with your partner', 'Osaka', 'img/countries/Japan/img-1.jpg', NULL, 'Osaka is a large port city and commercial center on the Japanese island of Honshu. It\'s known for its modern architecture, nightlife and hearty street food.', 1233),
(4, 'Great wall of china', 20, 'China', 'Cultural', 'The Great Wall of China is an ancient wall in China. The wall is made of cement, rocks, bricks, and powdered dirt. It was finished in 1878 and it was meant to protect the north of the empire of China from enemy attacks. It is the longest structure humans have ever built.', 'Beijing', 'img/countries/China/img-2.jpg', NULL, 'Beijing, China\'s sprawling capital, has history stretching back 3 millennia. Yet it\'s known as much for modern architecture as its ancient sites such as the grand Forbidden City complex, the imperial palace during the Ming and Qing dynasties. Nearby, the massive Tiananmen Square pedestrian plaza is the site of Mao Zedong\'s mausoleum and the National Museum of China, displaying a vast collection of cultural relics.', 458),
(5, 'Forbidden City', 9, 'China', 'Cultural', 'The Forbidden City is the palatial heart of China. Constructed in 1420, during the early Ming Dynasty, it is China\'s best-preserved imperial palace, and the largest ancient palatial structure in the world.', 'Beijing', 'img/countries/China/img-1.jpg', NULL, 'Beijing, China\'s sprawling capital, has history stretching back 3 millennia. Yet it\'s known as much for modern architecture as its ancient sites such as the grand Forbidden City complex, the imperial palace during the Ming and Qing dynasties. Nearby, the massive Tiananmen Square pedestrian plaza is the site of Mao Zedong\'s mausoleum and the National Museum of China, displaying a vast collection of cultural relics.', 458),
(6, 'Beijing hutong', 200, 'China', 'Night Life', 'The old lanes of the Beijing hutongs, many laid out hundreds of years ago during the Ming and Qing dynasty eras (1368-1912), retain some of the traditional culture and way of life of the past. Visiting the Beijing hutongs for shopping, dining, and experiencing the street life is a way to get in touch with the everyday people and experience the daily life of people in Beijing.', 'Beijing', 'img/countries/China/img-2.jpg', NULL, 'Beijing, China\'s sprawling capital, has history stretching back 3 millennia. Yet it\'s known as much for modern architecture as its ancient sites such as the grand Forbidden City complex, the imperial palace during the Ming and Qing dynasties. Nearby, the massive Tiananmen Square pedestrian plaza is the site of Mao Zedong\'s mausoleum and the National Museum of China, displaying a vast collection of cultural relics.', 458),
(7, 'Tiannamen Square', 19, 'China', 'Cultural', 'The Tiananmen Square protests were student-led demonstrations calling for democracy, free speech and a free press in China. They were halted in a bloody crackdown, known as the Tiananmen Square Massacre, by the Chinese government on June 4 and 5, 1989.', 'Beijing', 'img/countries/China/img-1.jpg', NULL, 'Beijing, China\'s sprawling capital, has history stretching back 3 millennia. Yet it\'s known as much for modern architecture as its ancient sites such as the grand Forbidden City complex, the imperial palace during the Ming and Qing dynasties. Nearby, the massive Tiananmen Square pedestrian plaza is the site of Mao Zedong\'s mausoleum and the National Museum of China, displaying a vast collection of cultural relics.', 458),
(8, 'Kung Fu Show ', 50, 'China', 'Night Life', 'As the capital of China,Beijing city is China\'s political cultural center as well as a transport and international exchange hub. It has 3000 years of history. This ancient, young, solemn, and yet charming famous city of culture draws millions of domestic and overseas tourists all the year round.', 'Beijing', 'img/countries/China/img-2.jpg', NULL, 'Beijing, China\'s sprawling capital, has history stretching back 3 millennia. Yet it\'s known as much for modern architecture as its ancient sites such as the grand Forbidden City complex, the imperial palace during the Ming and Qing dynasties. Nearby, the massive Tiananmen Square pedestrian plaza is the site of Mao Zedong\'s mausoleum and the National Museum of China, displaying a vast collection of cultural relics.', 458),
(10, 'Wang fujing ', 50, 'China', 'Night Life', 'Wangfujing Snack Street, located on the south side of Wangfujing Haoyou Emporium, is the ultimate place for enjoying famous snacks from all over China. There are also many shops and booths in the street specializing in tourist souvenirs, folk crafts and so on. Entrance to. Wangfujing Snack Street.', 'Beijing', 'img/countries/China/img-1.jpg', NULL, 'Beijing, China\'s sprawling capital, has history stretching back 3 millennia. Yet it\'s known as much for modern architecture as its ancient sites such as the grand Forbidden City complex, the imperial palace during the Ming and Qing dynasties. Nearby, the massive Tiananmen Square pedestrian plaza is the site of Mao Zedong\'s mausoleum and the National Museum of China, displaying a vast collection of cultural relics.', 458),
(11, 'Mae Ping River', 500, 'Thailand', 'Romance', 'The Mae Ping River cuts through Chiang Mai just a few blocks east of the old city and night market, where its banks have been developed with hotels, open-air restaurants, and bars. As it passes through the countryside, the river retains its natural charms. The ancient city of Wiang Kum Kam is also set on its shores south of Chiang Mai.', 'Chiang mai', 'img/countries/Thailand/img-2.jpg', NULL, 'Chiang Mai is a city in mountainous northern Thailand. Founded in 1296, it was capital of the independent Lanna Kingdom until 1558. Its Old City area still retains vestiges of walls and moats from its history as a cultural and religious center. ', 1766),
(12, 'Kata Beach', 19, 'Thailand', 'Adventure', 'Kata Beach is a 1.5-km strip of golden sand and is considered one of the most popular beaches in Phuket due to its combination of beauty, facilities and activities. Hundreds of people come each day to soak up the sun and swim in the sea.', 'Phuket', 'img/countries/Thailand/img-1.jpg', NULL, 'Phuket City, on Phuket Island, is the capital of Thailand\'s Phuket Province. In the Old Town, Thalang Road is lined with colorful 19th-century shophouses and Sino-Portuguese buildings. Built in 1903 by a wealthy tin merchant, Baan Chinpracha mansion has Italian floor tiles, shuttered windows and antique furniture. ', 2670),
(13, ' Wang Na Palace', 600, 'Thailand', 'Cultural', 'The Front Palace of the Rattankosin Period, or Wang Na, is also known as \"Bovorn Sathan Mongkol Palace\" refers to both a place (the residence of the King\'s Viceroy), as well as to an individual who holds the position of Viceroy.', 'Bangkok', 'img/countries/Thailand/img-2.jpg', NULL, 'Bangkok, Thailand\'s capital, is a large city known for ornate shrines and vibrant street life. The boat-filled Chao Phraya River feeds its network of canals, flowing past the Rattanakosin royal district, home to opulent Grand Palace and its sacred Wat Phra Kaew Temple.', 1277),
(14, ' Kinkakuji Temple', 400, 'Japan', 'Cultural', 'Zen temple in northern Kyoto whose top two floors are completely covered in gold leaf. Formally known as Rokuonji, the temple was the retirement villa of the shogun Ashikaga Yoshimitsu, and according to his will it became a Zen temple of the Rinzai sect after his death in 1408', 'Kyoto', 'img/countries/Japan/img-2.jpg', NULL, 'Kyoto, once the capital of Japan, is a city on the island of Honshu. It\'s famous for its numerous classical Buddhist temples, as well as gardens, imperial palaces, Shinto shrines and traditional wooden houses. It\'s also known for formal traditions such as kaiseki dining, consisting of multiple courses of precise dishes, and geisha, female entertainers often found in the Gion district.', 400),
(15, ' Ginza Mitsukoshi', 70, 'Japan', 'Shopping', 'The oldest surviving department store chain in Japan (founded 1673), Mitsukoshi has its gargantuan flagship store in Nihonbashi. This Ginza branch (opposite Wako) has womenswear and accessories on the first five floors, menswear on the sixth, and household goods on the seventh.', 'Tokyo', 'img/countries/Japan/img-1.jpg', NULL, 'Tokyo, Japan\'s busy capital, mixes the ultramodern and the traditional, from neon-lit skyscrapers to historic temples. The opulent Meiji Shinto Shrine is known for its towering gate and surrounding woods. The Imperial Palace sits amid large public gardens. ', 2245),
(16, 'Namsan Tower', 9, 'Korea', 'Romance', 'It is the highest point in Seoul, offering 360-degree views of the entire city. It was also the very first general radio wave tower in South Korea and continues to broadcast signals for media outlets such as SBS, MBC, KBS, and FM. Construction on Namsan Tower began back in 1969 and the tower began broadcasting in 1971.', 'Seoul', 'img/countries/Korea/img-2.jpg', NULL, 'Seoul, the capital of South Korea, is a huge metropolis where modern skyscrapers, high-tech subways and pop culture meet Buddhist temples, palaces and street markets. Notable attractions include futuristic Dongdaemun Design Plaza, a convention hall with curving architecture and a rooftop park; Gyeongbokgung Palace, which once had more than 7,000 rooms; and Jogyesa Temple, site of ancient locust and pine trees. ', 2999),
(17, ' Busan Aquarium', 55, 'Korea', 'Cultural', 'Sea Life Busan Aquarium is an aquarium located in Haeundae Beach, South Korea. There are about 250 species and up to 35,000 marine animals on display. The main tank contains 3,000,000 litres (790,000 US gal) of water, and the animals can be viewed through acrylic windows or from the 80-metre (260 ft) underwater tunnel.', 'Busan', 'img/countries/Korea/img-1.jpg', NULL, 'Busan, a large port city in South Korea, is known for its beaches, mountains and temples. Busy Haeundae Beach features the Sea Life Aquarium, plus a Folk Square with traditional games such as tug-of-war, while Gwangalli Beach has many bars and views of modern Diamond Bridge.', 1344),
(18, 'Summer Palace', 80, 'China', 'Cultural', 'The Summer Palace is really accessible from the city, all you have to do is take Line 4 north to Xiyuan or Beigongmen Stations. Head to the UNESCO World Heritage site of the Summer Palace, the imperial gardens and palaces from the Qing Dynasty. ', 'Beijing', 'img/countries/China/img-1.jpg', NULL, 'Beijing, China\'s sprawling capital, has history stretching back 3 millennia. Yet it\'s known as much for modern architecture as its ancient sites such as the grand Forbidden City complex, the imperial palace during the Ming and Qing dynasties. Nearby, the massive Tiananmen Square pedestrian plaza is the site of Mao Zedong\'s mausoleum and the National Museum of China, displaying a vast collection of cultural relics.', 458),
(19, 'Yeouido Han River Park', 250, 'Korea', 'Romance', 'A regular haunt for both locals and tourists alike, the Yeouido Han River Park is exceptionally beautiful during Spring, with cherry blossoms flourishing and decorating the park. Coupled with the cool weather and performances by buskers, you\'ll definitely feel like you\'re the lead in a romantic Korean drama here! Take a day in your Seoul itinerary to engage in outdoor activities at Yeouido Han River Park.', 'Seoul', 'img/countries/Korea/img-2.jpg', NULL, 'Seoul, the capital of South Korea, is a huge metropolis where modern skyscrapers, high-tech subways and pop culture meet Buddhist temples, palaces and street markets. Notable attractions include futuristic Dongdaemun Design Plaza, a convention hall with curving architecture and a rooftop park; Gyeongbokgung Palace, which once had more than 7,000 rooms; and Jogyesa Temple, site of ancient locust and pine trees. ', 2999),
(20, 'Namsangol Hanok Village', 645, 'Korea', 'Cultural', 'Namsangol Hanok Village is highly detailed with extra special care and attention being given to the decorations for each home, which are furnished with both era-appropriate and social status appropriate household items. Made up of traditional homes, called hanok, you can imagine what it was once like to live in a traditional, Joseon-era Korean village as you explore this historical attraction.', 'Seoul', 'img/countries/Korea/img-1.jpg', NULL, 'Seoul, the capital of South Korea, is a huge metropolis where modern skyscrapers, high-tech subways and pop culture meet Buddhist temples, palaces and street markets. Notable attractions include futuristic Dongdaemun Design Plaza, a convention hall with curving architecture and a rooftop park; Gyeongbokgung Palace, which once had more than 7,000 rooms; and Jogyesa Temple, site of ancient locust and pine trees. ', 2999),
(21, 'N Seoul Tower', 550, 'Korea', 'Cultural', 'Make your way over to the N Seoul Tower, which is also known as the Namsan Tower (or Seoul Tower), and head up to the observatory. At nearly 480 meters above sea level, the N Seoul Tower is one of the highest towers in Asia and offers unparalleled views of the city.', 'Seoul', 'img/countries/Korea/img-2.jpg', NULL, 'Seoul, the capital of South Korea, is a huge metropolis where modern skyscrapers, high-tech subways and pop culture meet Buddhist temples, palaces and street markets. Notable attractions include futuristic Dongdaemun Design Plaza, a convention hall with curving architecture and a rooftop park; Gyeongbokgung Palace, which once had more than 7,000 rooms; and Jogyesa Temple, site of ancient locust and pine trees. ', 2999),
(22, 'Garosu-gil', 100, 'Korea', 'Shopping', 'Garosu-gil is a must-go when you visit Seoul. Located in Gangnam, Garosu-gil is a fashion-forward shopping district with endless quaint cafes and indie local fashion designer stores tucked in every corner! It\'s also located near entertainment agencies, and many celebrities have been sighted shopping here, including popular K-pop group EXO.', 'Seoul', 'img/countries/Korea/img-1.jpg', NULL, 'Seoul, the capital of South Korea, is a huge metropolis where modern skyscrapers, high-tech subways and pop culture meet Buddhist temples, palaces and street markets. Notable attractions include futuristic Dongdaemun Design Plaza, a convention hall with curving architecture and a rooftop park; Gyeongbokgung Palace, which once had more than 7,000 rooms; and Jogyesa Temple, site of ancient locust and pine trees. ', 2999),
(23, 'Cheonggyecheon Stream', 645, 'Korea', 'Romance', 'For a taste of Seoul\'s local dating scene, visit the Cheonggyecheon Stream. An urban renewal project, this 8.4 km long stream is more than 15 feet below ground. It serves as a hidden oasis in the bustling city center of Seoul. Many couples enjoy taking a walk by this stream, especially during the evening. The pretty lights and fountains along the way add extra elements of romance to your night stroll.', 'Seoul', 'img/countries/Korea/img-1.jpg', NULL, 'Seoul, the capital of South Korea, is a huge metropolis where modern skyscrapers, high-tech subways and pop culture meet Buddhist temples, palaces and street markets. Notable attractions include futuristic Dongdaemun Design Plaza, a convention hall with curving architecture and a rooftop park; Gyeongbokgung Palace, which once had more than 7,000 rooms; and Jogyesa Temple, site of ancient locust and pine trees. ', 2999),
(24, 'All That Jazz', 800, 'Korea', 'Night Life', 'Often called the \"granddaddy of jazz bars in Korea,\" All That Jazz is a local legend that opened in 1976. The venue has hosted many big names, such as saxophone player Jung Sungjo and drummer Ryu Boksung, before they became famous. Boksung, in fact, still plays onstage every other Saturday.', 'Seoul', 'img/countries/Korea/img-1.jpg', NULL, 'Seoul, the capital of South Korea, is a huge metropolis where modern skyscrapers, high-tech subways and pop culture meet Buddhist temples, palaces and street markets. Notable attractions include futuristic Dongdaemun Design Plaza, a convention hall with curving architecture and a rooftop park; Gyeongbokgung Palace, which once had more than 7,000 rooms; and Jogyesa Temple, site of ancient locust and pine trees. ', 2999),
(25, 'Shinsekai District', 220, 'Japan', 'Night Life', 'At night, one thing immediately stands out in Shinsekai, the large colourful and grotesque signs of many restaurants and bars. This area comes into its own at night when the large neon lights and decorate figurines lit up the sky. Try the traditional Kushi-katsu in the area.', 'Tokyo', 'img/countries/Japan/img-2.jpg', NULL, 'Tokyo, Japan\'s busy capital, mixes the ultramodern and the traditional, from neon-lit skyscrapers to historic temples. The opulent Meiji Shinto Shrine is known for its towering gate and surrounding woods. The Imperial Palace sits amid large public gardens. ', 2245),
(26, 'Maruyama-koen Park', 645, 'Japan', 'Nature', 'Embark to Maruyama-koen park to take a look at the Gion Shidare Zakura, Kyoto\'s most famous cherry tree, take some nice photos around this area before heading west to view the grand and colourful Yasaka-jinja Shrine. Have lunch in the area and continue exploring the shrines nearby and indulge in some light shopping.', 'Tokyo', 'img/countries/Japan/img-1.jpg', NULL, 'Tokyo, Japan\'s busy capital, mixes the ultramodern and the traditional, from neon-lit skyscrapers to historic temples. The opulent Meiji Shinto Shrine is known for its towering gate and surrounding woods. The Imperial Palace sits amid large public gardens. ', 2245),
(27, 'Arashiyama Bamboo Grove', 100, 'Japan', 'Nature', 'Start the day early and have a hearty breakfast before travelling to the Arashiyama Bamboo Grove, also known as the Bamboo Forest. Experience the magical place when walking through in between tall bamboo stalks while enjoying the morning breeze and the fresh air.', 'Tokyo', 'img/countries/Japan/img-2.jpg', NULL, 'Tokyo, Japan\'s busy capital, mixes the ultramodern and the traditional, from neon-lit skyscrapers to historic temples. The opulent Meiji Shinto Shrine is known for its towering gate and surrounding woods. The Imperial Palace sits amid large public gardens. ', 2245),
(28, 'Yoyogi Park', 50, 'Japan', 'Adventure', 'Take a stroll at Yoyogi park! If it is the right season to be there, treat your eyes to a colourful display of cherry blossoms. On other seasons, it is also an ideal location to have a picnic or just relax and bask in the atmosphere. \r\n', 'Tokyo', 'img/countries/Japan/img-2.jpg', NULL, 'Tokyo, Japan\'s busy capital, mixes the ultramodern and the traditional, from neon-lit skyscrapers to historic temples. The opulent Meiji Shinto Shrine is known for its towering gate and surrounding woods. The Imperial Palace sits amid large public gardens. ', 2245),
(29, 'Osaka Castle', 490, 'Japan', 'Adventure', 'Travel to Osaka Castle, initially intended to be the center of Japan. The castle survived the war by miraculously surviving the city wide air raids. The castle tower is now entirely modern on the inside and even features an elevator for easier accessibility. Spend some time taking photos before heading to Namba City for a night of evening shopping.\r\n', 'Tokyo', 'img/countries/Japan/img-2.jpg', NULL, 'Tokyo, Japan\'s busy capital, mixes the ultramodern and the traditional, from neon-lit skyscrapers to historic temples. The opulent Meiji Shinto Shrine is known for its towering gate and surrounding woods. The Imperial Palace sits amid large public gardens. ', 2245),
(30, 'Harajuku Shopping', 670, 'Japan', 'Shopping', 'Take the JR line located right beside the park to Harajuku, where you will head into Takeshita Street, the busiest shopping street in Tokyo! Consisting of cute character-theme cafes. Trendy shops and Instagram-worthy food, you will be spoilt for choice at this location!\r\n', 'Tokyo', 'img/countries/Japan/img-2.jpg', NULL, 'Tokyo, Japan\'s busy capital, mixes the ultramodern and the traditional, from neon-lit skyscrapers to historic temples. The opulent Meiji Shinto Shrine is known for its towering gate and surrounding woods. The Imperial Palace sits amid large public gardens. ', 2245),
(31, 'Bungee Jumping', 300, 'Thailand', 'Adventure', 'Get your adrenaline fix while in Phuket with Jungle Bungee Jump. Experience the thrill of bungy jumping from a height of 164 feet (50 meters) and enjoy spectacular views as you swing over a natural lake in the heart of the jungle. Full instruction is provided, and you will receive a personalized bungy jump certificate as proof of your accomplishment.', 'Phuket', 'img/countries/Thailand/img-1.jpg', NULL, 'Phuket City, on Phuket Island, is the capital of Thailand\'s Phuket Province. In the Old Town, Thalang Road is lined with colorful 19th-century shophouses and Sino-Portuguese buildings. Built in 1903 by a wealthy tin merchant, Baan Chinpracha mansion has Italian floor tiles, shuttered windows and antique furniture. ', 2670),
(33, 'Night Market', 480, 'Thailand', 'Night Life', 'Strolling along a night market in Phuket is one the most authentic experiences you can have. You\'ll get everything under the sun (and more) here, from funky souvenirs to cheap clothing. If you want to savour the best street food Phuket has to offer, these night markets are ideal', 'Phuket', 'img/countries/Thailand/img-2.jpg', NULL, 'Phuket City, on Phuket Island, is the capital of Thailand\'s Phuket Province. In the Old Town, Thalang Road is lined with colorful 19th-century shophouses and Sino-Portuguese buildings. Built in 1903 by a wealthy tin merchant, Baan Chinpracha mansion has Italian floor tiles, shuttered windows and antique furniture. ', 2670),
(34, 'Doi Inthanon National Park', 780, 'Thailand', 'Romance', 'When in the mountainous region of Chiang Mai, what better way to explore the area than by checking out the mountain scenery and indigenous tribes in the area? This is romance with a dash of adventure at its best!', 'Phuket', 'img/countries/Thailand/img-1.jpg', NULL, 'Phuket City, on Phuket Island, is the capital of Thailand\'s Phuket Province. In the Old Town, Thalang Road is lined with colorful 19th-century shophouses and Sino-Portuguese buildings. Built in 1903 by a wealthy tin merchant, Baan Chinpracha mansion has Italian floor tiles, shuttered windows and antique furniture. ', 2670),
(35, 'Bangkok Art and Culture Center', 230, 'Thailand', 'Cultural', 'This museum focuses on Thai culture, with highlights that include a large collection of musical instruments, recorded music, ornate royal funeral chariots, and impressive wooden carvings. The museum isn\'t very big and the signs aren\'t very detailed, but the artifacts are interesting to look at.', 'Phuket', 'img/countries/Thailand/img-2.jpg', NULL, 'Phuket City, on Phuket Island, is the capital of Thailand\'s Phuket Province. In the Old Town, Thalang Road is lined with colorful 19th-century shophouses and Sino-Portuguese buildings. Built in 1903 by a wealthy tin merchant, Baan Chinpracha mansion has Italian floor tiles, shuttered windows and antique furniture. ', 2670),
(36, 'Khao Sok National Park', 100, 'Thailand', 'Nature', 'Khao Sok is perfectly situated on the mainland between Phuket, Krabi, Khao Lak and Koh Samui, the most popular destinations in Southern Thailand. It is a fantastic place to go on vacation. Close and personal elephant encounters, jungle trekking on foot and canoeing are all possible activities, which will give you the experience of a lifetime.\r\n', 'Phuket', 'img/countries/Thailand/img-2.jpg', NULL, 'Phuket City, on Phuket Island, is the capital of Thailand\'s Phuket Province. In the Old Town, Thalang Road is lined with colorful 19th-century shophouses and Sino-Portuguese buildings. Built in 1903 by a wealthy tin merchant, Baan Chinpracha mansion has Italian floor tiles, shuttered windows and antique furniture. ', 2670),
(37, 'Siam Paragon', 780, 'Thailand', 'Shopping', 'For designer clothes and upscale shopping, Siam Paragon has a wide range of stores, as well as restaurants and a luxurious movie theater (the best in the country, in my opinion). Siam Ocean World aquarium (the largest aquarium in Southeast Asia) is located on the bottom floor and is a good family activity if you are traveling with kids. There is a large (but slightly overpriced) food court here too.', 'Phuket', 'img/countries/Thailand/img-2.jpg', NULL, 'Phuket City, on Phuket Island, is the capital of Thailand\'s Phuket Province. In the Old Town, Thalang Road is lined with colorful 19th-century shophouses and Sino-Portuguese buildings. Built in 1903 by a wealthy tin merchant, Baan Chinpracha mansion has Italian floor tiles, shuttered windows and antique furniture. ', 2670),
(38, 'Aozora Sandaime', 50, 'Japan', 'Shopping', 'Head down to Ginza, the Orchard Road equivalent of Japan. Enjoy a large range of variety for shopping ranging from department stores to luxury brands. Spend the entire afternoon here and go crazy with your shopping!\r\n\r\nDinner will be located in Ginza as well, enjoy sushi in Aozora Sandaime Ginzamitsukoshiten, famous Sushi bar where even the prime minister of Japan dine in! Continue shopping around the area before heading back to the hotel with your loots.\r\n', 'Tokyo', 'img/countries/Japan/img-2.jpg', NULL, 'Tokyo, Japan\'\'s busy capital, mixes the ultramodern and the traditional, from neon-lit skyscrapers to historic temples. The opulent Meiji Shinto Shrine is known for its towering gate and surrounding woods. The Imperial Palace sits amid large public gardens. ', 1233),
(39, 'Yoyogi Park', 100, 'Japan', 'Shopping', 'Take a stroll at Ueno park! If it is the right season to be there, treat your eyes to a colourful display of cherry blossoms. On other seasons, it is also an ideal location to have a picnic or just relax and bask in the atmosphere. \r\n\r\nAfter relaxing to your content, take the JR line located right beside the park to Harajuku, where you will head into Takeshita Street, the busiest shopping street in Tokyo! Consisting of cute character-theme cafes. Trendy shops and Instagram-worthy food, you will be spoilt for choice at this location!\r\n', 'Tokyo', 'img/countries/Japan/img-2.jpg', NULL, 'Tokyo, Japan\'\'s busy capital, mixes the ultramodern and the traditional, from neon-lit skyscrapers to historic temples. The opulent Meiji Shinto Shrine is known for its towering gate and surrounding woods. The Imperial Palace sits amid large public gardens. ', 1233),
(40, 'Asakusa', 100, 'Japan', 'Shopping', 'Take a trip down to Asakusa, one of the oldest towns in Tokyo, also home to the famous Dango in Japan. Spend the day walking around this old town with lots to offer ranging from shopping to sights in the Tokyo tower where you will be treated with the view of the city from atop one of the tallest buildings in Japan. \r\nBefore dinner, make a trip to Sensoji Temple where there will be many shops located nearby and also restaurants where you will be spoilt for choice after exploring the big temple. This will be the perfect time to buy souvenirs for friends and family at home.\r\n\r\nEnjoy a walk beside the River at night to look at all the nightlights from the tower and city itself before heading back to the hotel to have a rest.\r\n', 'Tokyo', 'img/countries/Japan/img-2.jpg', NULL, 'Tokyo, Japan\'\'s busy capital, mixes the ultramodern and the traditional, from neon-lit skyscrapers to historic temples. The opulent Meiji Shinto Shrine is known for its towering gate and surrounding woods. The Imperial Palace sits amid large public gardens. ', 1233),
(41, 'Shinjuku', 100, 'Japan', 'Shopping', 'Spend the day in Shinjuku, a place that needs no further introduction. A photo worthy cross junction where you are free to walk in any direction when the traffic light turns red. This is a shopping paradise for people of all ages. Have lunch at the famous Ichiran Ramen which originated from this shop in Shinjuku. \r\n\r\nAfter a hearty afternoon lunch, enjoy a quick coffee break at Starbucks, located at the second floor. There, you can spend some time people watching while relaxing and recharging for another shopping spree. \r\n\r\nAfter the coffee break, head down the street where you will find department stores and familiar brands such as Adidas, H&M and Nike etc. Spend the entire Afternoon filling up your luggages with shopping!\r\n', 'Tokyo', 'img/countries/Japan/img-1.jpg', NULL, 'Tokyo, Japan\'\'s busy capital, mixes the ultramodern and the traditional, from neon-lit skyscrapers to historic temples. The opulent Meiji Shinto Shrine is known for its towering gate and surrounding woods. The Imperial Palace sits amid large public gardens. ', 1233),
(42, 'Akihabara', 100, 'Japan', 'Shopping', 'Located near to Shinjuku and Harajuku, take a trip down to Akihabara, the entertainment district for Japan, here you will find many themed restaurants and shopping opportunities for toys, gifts and many more. Have fun watching people who dress up as cartoon characters and famous movie characters here. This place is lively and offers many things to do. \r\n\r\nNext, move on to Odaiba, a reclaimed island in Japan where there is much shopping to do, also known as the factory outlets for luxury brands, you can purchase countless amounts of items here at a very huge slashed price. Food here is also plenty and you can choose what to eat based on your budget.\r\n', 'Tokyo', 'img/countries/Japan/img-1.jpg', NULL, 'Tokyo, Japan\'\'s busy capital, mixes the ultramodern and the traditional, from neon-lit skyscrapers to historic temples. The opulent Meiji Shinto Shrine is known for its towering gate and surrounding woods. The Imperial Palace sits amid large public gardens. ', 1233),
(43, 'Dotonburi', 100, 'Japan', 'Night Life', 'Enjoy the hotel buffet before taking the JR transport to Shin-Osaka where you will enjoy amazing food and also shopping in famous malls such as Isetan etc.\r\n\r\nAfter lunch, embark to Dotonburi, a famous shopping street in Japan, you will most likely be spending the entire evening here on food and also shopping, bask in the atmosphere and amazing lights in the area before heading back to the hotel with a happy stomach. \r\n', 'Osaka', 'img/countries/Japan/img-1.jpg', NULL, 'Tokyo, Japan\'\'s busy capital, mixes the ultramodern and the traditional, from neon-lit skyscrapers to historic temples. The opulent Meiji Shinto Shrine is known for its towering gate and surrounding woods. The Imperial Palace sits amid large public gardens. ', 1999),
(44, 'Shinsaibashi', 100, 'Japan', 'Night Life', 'Spend the day navigating around Osaka with your JR pass, most stations are easily accessible and with many things to do, in the evening, head to Shinsaibashi, another prominent shopping district in the heart of Osaka and beside Dotonburi. Here, you will be able to count countless amounts of shops selling things ranging from cosmetics to shoes as well as eateries and bars, you will not have to worry about an empty stomach. Enjoy the bustling atmospthere at night and you can also choose to navigate to Dotonburi should you not have enough things to purchase.', 'Osaka', 'img/countries/Japan/img-1.jpg', NULL, 'Tokyo, Japan\'\'s busy capital, mixes the ultramodern and the traditional, from neon-lit skyscrapers to historic temples. The opulent Meiji Shinto Shrine is known for its towering gate and surrounding woods. The Imperial Palace sits amid large public gardens. ', 1999),
(45, 'Hozenji Temple', 100, 'Japan', 'Night Life', 'In the morning, travel to Hozenji Temple which is famous for the Fudo Myo-o statue. It became famous after it survived the World War bombings, up north of the temple wil be the popular Hozenji Yokocho alley where walking through the stone-paved narrow alley will allow you to have a good impression of how it feels to have lived in Osaka a hundred years ago.This area is best to explore after dark when the bars and restaurants are opened and have all lit their old fashioned lanterns.\r\n', 'Osaka', 'img/countries/Japan/img-1.jpg', NULL, 'Tokyo, Japan\'\'s busy capital, mixes the ultramodern and the traditional, from neon-lit skyscrapers to historic temples. The opulent Meiji Shinto Shrine is known for its towering gate and surrounding woods. The Imperial Palace sits amid large public gardens. ', 1999),
(46, 'Shinsekai District', 100, 'Japan', 'Night Life', 'Feel free to sleep in or enjoy the streets near the hotel before embarking to Shinsekai District, an area developed before the war and largely untouched afterward. This is the place to go to experience retro Osaka ambiance. Spend the afternoon in the area exploring and taking photos. \r\n\r\nAt night, one thing immediately stands out in Shinsekai, the large colourful and grotesque signs of many restaurants and bars. This area comes into its own at night when the large neon lights and decorate figurines lit up the sky. Try the traditional Kushi-katsu in the area. You can also choose to visit Spa World, a huge bath complex with a large number of onsen from around the world which will be enjoyed naked and gender-separated. \r\n', 'Osaka', 'img/countries/Japan/img-1.jpg', NULL, 'Tokyo, Japan\'\'s busy capital, mixes the ultramodern and the traditional, from neon-lit skyscrapers to historic temples. The opulent Meiji Shinto Shrine is known for its towering gate and surrounding woods. The Imperial Palace sits amid large public gardens. ', 1999),
(47, 'Castle', 100, 'Japan', 'Night Life', 'Enjoy a hotel buffet in the morning before heading out. Travel to Osaka Castle, initially intended to be the center of Japan. The castle survived the war by miraculously surviving the city wide air raids. The castle tower is now entirely modern on the inside and even features an elevator for easier accessibility. Spend some time taking photos before heading to Namba City for a night of evening shopping.\r\n\r\nThat area allows many selection for food as well as alcohol for those interested. Spend the evening in the area shopping and enjoying the food and sights before going back to the hotel for rests. \r\n', 'Osaka', 'img/countries/Japan/img-1.jpg', NULL, 'Tokyo, Japan\'\'s busy capital, mixes the ultramodern and the traditional, from neon-lit skyscrapers to historic temples. The opulent Meiji Shinto Shrine is known for its towering gate and surrounding woods. The Imperial Palace sits amid large public gardens. ', 1999),
(48, 'District Shopping', 100, 'Japan', 'Night Life', 'Feel free to sleep in or enjoy the streets near the hotel before embarking to Shinsekai District, an area developed before the war and largely untouched afterward. This is the place to go to experience retro Osaka ambiance. Spend the afternoon in the area exploring and taking photos. \r\n\r\nAt night, one thing immediately stands out in Shinsekai, the large colourful and grotesque signs of many restaurants and bars. This area comes into its own at night when the large neon lights and decorate figurines lit up the sky. Try the traditional Kushi-katsu in the area. You can also choose to visit Spa World, a huge bath complex with a large number of onsen from around the world which will be enjoyed naked and gender-separate\r\n', 'Osaka', 'img/countries/Japan/img-1.jpg', NULL, 'Tokyo, Japan\'\'s busy capital, mixes the ultramodern and the traditional, from neon-lit skyscrapers to historic temples. The opulent Meiji Shinto Shrine is known for its towering gate and surrounding woods. The Imperial Palace sits amid large public gardens. ', 1999),
(49, 'Maruyama-Koen Park', 100, 'Japan', 'Nature', 'Rise and shine! Enjoy the hotel’s hearty buffet and get your energy levels up before the day’s activities. Embark to Maruyama-koen park to take a look at the Gion Shidare Zakura, Kyoto’s most famous cherry tree, take some nice photos around this area before heading west to view the grand and colourful Yasaka-jinja Shrine. Have lunch in the area and continue exploring the shrines nearby and indulge in some light shopping.\r\n\r\nIn the evening, head back to the hotel area to enjoy some food around the vicinity before heading back to the hotel to conclude the day’s activities.\r\n', 'Kyoto', 'img/countries/Japan/img-1.jpg', NULL, 'Tokyo, Japan\'\'s busy capital, mixes the ultramodern and the traditional, from neon-lit skyscrapers to historic temples. The opulent Meiji Shinto Shrine is known for its towering gate and surrounding woods. The Imperial Palace sits amid large public gardens. ', 888),
(50, 'Nishiki Market', 100, 'Japan', 'Nature', 'Have breakfast in the hotel before taking a trip to Nishiki Market. A famous location in Kyoto. You will be able to find a large variety of Japanese delights in the area, you can also opt to purchase the market tour which will allow you to learn more about Japan culture as well as the origin of Kyoto’s famous cuisine and snacks. Feel free to enjoy lunch in any of the eateries around the area. \r\n\r\nIn the evening, head back to downtown Kyoto for a stroll at the geisha district Gion, if you are lucky, you will be able to spot a real geisha. There will be a lot of options for dining in Gion, ranging from upscale restaurants serving tradition Kyoto cuisine to weird and wonderful restaurants that would be sure to delight your taste buds. \r\n\r\nAfter dinner, you can choose to continue to walk around the Gion area or head back to the hotel to conclude the day. \r\n', 'Kyoto', 'img/countries/Japan/img-1.jpg', NULL, 'Tokyo, Japan\'\'s busy capital, mixes the ultramodern and the traditional, from neon-lit skyscrapers to historic temples. The opulent Meiji Shinto Shrine is known for its towering gate and surrounding woods. The Imperial Palace sits amid large public gardens. ', 888),
(51, 'Imperial Palace Park', 100, 'Japan', 'Nature', 'Start the day with breakfast in the hotel and travel to Kyoto Imperial Palace Park, located near the Imperial Palace, a very popular destination whenever it is Cherry Blossom season. The garden is a lovely place to enjoy a picnic. Have a zen afternoon here basking in the atmosphere.\r\n\r\nAfter lunch, head to Nijo-jo Castle, built in the Edo period and was meant to show off the power and influence of the Shogun Warlords,\r\n', 'Kyoto', 'img/countries/Japan/img-1.jpg', NULL, 'Tokyo, Japan\'\'s busy capital, mixes the ultramodern and the traditional, from neon-lit skyscrapers to historic temples. The opulent Meiji Shinto Shrine is known for its towering gate and surrounding woods. The Imperial Palace sits amid large public gardens. ', 888),
(52, 'Train Station', 100, 'Japan', 'Nature', 'Have a good sleep and wake up at your own timing, after having lunch, proceed to Kyoto Station with your belongings and spend some time there, the place is worth a visit for its famous modern architecture made of steel-and-glass. The hundreds of shop and varied selection of restaurants.  Make sure to go up the 15th floor where there is an observation deck with a nice view of Kyoto.\r\nProceed to take the express train back to Osaka or Tokyo depending on where your flight is.\r\n', 'Kyoto', 'img/countries/Japan/img-1.jpg', NULL, 'Tokyo, Japan\'\'s busy capital, mixes the ultramodern and the traditional, from neon-lit skyscrapers to historic temples. The opulent Meiji Shinto Shrine is known for its towering gate and surrounding woods. The Imperial Palace sits amid large public gardens. ', 888),
(53, 'Arashiyama Bamboo Grove', 100, 'Japan', 'Nature', 'Start the day early and have a hearty breakfast before travelling to the Arashiyama Bamboo Grove, also known as the Bamboo Forest. Experience the magical place when walking through in between tall bamboo stalks while enjoying the morning breeze and the fresh air. \r\n\r\nHave a quick lunch before proceeding to your next destination which is the Fushimi Inari Shrine, a stunning and atmospherical shrine that consists of thousands of red tori gates lined up as a pathway 4km up the mountain. Best visited in the afternoon when the light renders the gates at their most beautiful, you will spend your entire afternoon here taking amazing phots and walk up as far as your energy permits, just remember to walk back down.\r\n\r\nHave dinner in the vicinity at the small eateries before going back to the hotel.\r\n', 'Tokyo', 'img/countries/Japan/img-1.jpg', NULL, 'Tokyo, Japan\'\'s busy capital, mixes the ultramodern and the traditional, from neon-lit skyscrapers to historic temples. The opulent Meiji Shinto Shrine is known for its towering gate and surrounding woods. The Imperial Palace sits amid large public gardens. ', 888),
(54, 'Summer Palace', 100, 'China', 'Cultural', 'The Summer Palace is really accessible from the city, all you have to do is take Line 4 north to Xiyuan or Beigongmen Stations. The cost for the gardens is 30 RMB (4 USD/3.50 GBP) during summer months (April to October) and 20 RMB (2.75 USD/2.25 GBP) for the rest. There are several add on costs for access to different areas, but you can also purchase a combo ticket for 60 RMB/50 RMB (8.25/7.00 USD or 7.00/5.75 GBP) depending on the time of year.\r\n', 'Beijing', 'img/countries/China/img-1.jpg', NULL, 'Beijing, China\'\'s sprawling capital, has history stretching back 3 millennia. Yet it\'\'s known as much for modern architecture as its ancient sites such as the grand Forbidden City complex, the imperial palace during the Ming and Qing dynasties. Nearby, the massive Tiananmen Square pedestrian plaza is the site of Mao Zedong\'\'s mausoleum and the National Museum of China, displaying a vast collection of cultural relics.', 688),
(55, 'Jingshan Park', 100, 'China', 'Cultural', 'After that, You’ll have to exit the Forbidden City on the opposite side to where you entered. Which is great, as right across the road from this exit is Jingshan Park. One of the must do things in Beijing is to take a short walk up Prospect Hill, you’ll be afforded the best view back down over the Forbidden City, as well as a 360 degree view of the whole city. It’s a great way to understand the size and scale of Beijing.\r\n', 'Beijing', 'img/countries/China/img-1.jpg', NULL, 'Beijing, China\'\'s sprawling capital, has history stretching back 3 millennia. Yet it\'\'s known as much for modern architecture as its ancient sites such as the grand Forbidden City complex, the imperial palace during the Ming and Qing dynasties. Nearby, the massive Tiananmen Square pedestrian plaza is the site of Mao Zedong\'\'s mausoleum and the National Museum of China, displaying a vast collection of cultural relics.', 688),
(56, 'Tombs and Temples', 100, 'China', 'Cultural', 'The thirteen tombs of the Ming Dynasty are a short day trip from Beijing (around 50km), and the best way to start off your last day of your Beijing itinerary. You’ll either need to take a private car or a bus, and then walk around the massive area that houses the thirteen emperors of the Ming Dynasty, which ran between 1368 and 1644. It’s a huge area so either choose a guide or pick a few of the Ming tombs, else you’ll be there all day!\r\nA temple of many names – Lama, Yonghe, Harmony and Peace Palace – this temple in the north of Beijing is one of the most beautiful lamaseries (monastery for buddhist teachers) in all of China, and a great place to visit in Beijing. It was built in 1694 as the residence of Emperor Yongzheng but later became a lamasery in 1744, which it still operates as today.\r\nThis is a great stop after the tombs to take in a bit of peace and quiet, punctuated by the sound of monks and the smell of burning incense.\r\nRound the corner is also the Confucius Temple, if you’re keen to see another temple in the area – it’s the second largest Confucius temple in the country.\r\n', 'Beijing', 'img/countries/China/img-1.jpg', NULL, 'Beijing, China\'\'s sprawling capital, has history stretching back 3 millennia. Yet it\'\'s known as much for modern architecture as its ancient sites such as the grand Forbidden City complex, the imperial palace during the Ming and Qing dynasties. Nearby, the massive Tiananmen Square pedestrian plaza is the site of Mao Zedong\'\'s mausoleum and the National Museum of China, displaying a vast collection of cultural relics.', 688),
(57, 'Houhai Lake', 100, 'China', 'Cultural', 'Morning Branch at the Houhai Lake, afterwards walk around there. The street structure of Houhai was first formed in the Yuan Dynasty. Many buildings are very old and have the typical characteristics of traditional Beijing architecture.You can pay a visit to the former mansions of celebrities, such as Prince Gong\'s Mansion, the Former Residence of Guo Moruo, who was a great poet, and the Former Residence of Soong Ching-ling, who was the wife of Sun Yat-sen. You can also wander around the ancient lanes, such as Yandaixie Street and Nanluogu Lane.', 'Beijing', 'img/countries/China/img-1.jpg', NULL, 'Beijing, China\'\'s sprawling capital, has history stretching back 3 millennia. Yet it\'\'s known as much for modern architecture as its ancient sites such as the grand Forbidden City complex, the imperial palace during the Ming and Qing dynasties. Nearby, the massive Tiananmen Square pedestrian plaza is the site of Mao Zedong\'\'s mausoleum and the National Museum of China, displaying a vast collection of cultural relics.', 688),
(58, 'Beijing Zoo', 100, 'China', 'Night Life', 'Then Head to the Beijing zoo not too far from the center of Beijing and home to China’s national treasure: pandas.Beijing Zoo is a natural garden with dense groves of trees, stretches of grassland, a small stream, lotus pools and small hills dotted with pavilions and halls. It was called Wansheng Garden in the Qing Dynasty (literally it means the Garden of 10,000 animals). After the Qing Dynasty was replaced by the Republic of China in 1912, this former royal garden became an experimental area for farming and animal husbandry. The zoo was not established until 6 years after the founding of the P. R. China in 1955, when the garden was officially opened to visitors as the City Zoo of Beijing.\r\nAfter the zoo, we headed back to the massage salon for manicures and a full body massage, then grabbed dinner near by the zoo, then head back to the hotel.\r\n', 'Beijing', 'img/countries/China/img-1.jpg', NULL, 'Beijing, China\'\'s sprawling capital, has history stretching back 3 millennia. Yet it\'\'s known as much for modern architecture as its ancient sites such as the grand Forbidden City complex, the imperial palace during the Ming and Qing dynasties. Nearby, the massive Tiananmen Square pedestrian plaza is the site of Mao Zedong\'\'s mausoleum and the National Museum of China, displaying a vast collection of cultural relics.', 988),
(59, 'Tianzifang', 100, 'China', 'Night Life', 'After lunch can continue the second museum at the world expo museum, the architecture of the building is swoon worthy as a combination of glass, wood, and white stone. It’s free to visit the museum, all you need to do is get tickets from the northern hall and then go across to the exhibit. It showcases the different expos around the word in the last few centuries, in particular London, Paris, and the effect they have on the general public and, in particular, the host cities. The exhibits are spread over 5 floors ending with Shanghai expo. Then on the floors back down it’s exhibits from around the world.', 'Beijing', 'img/countries/China/img-1.jpg', NULL, 'Beijing, China\'\'s sprawling capital, has history stretching back 3 millennia. Yet it\'\'s known as much for modern architecture as its ancient sites such as the grand Forbidden City complex, the imperial palace during the Ming and Qing dynasties. Nearby, the massive Tiananmen Square pedestrian plaza is the site of Mao Zedong\'\'s mausoleum and the National Museum of China, displaying a vast collection of cultural relics.', 988),
(60, 'Longhua Temple', 100, 'China', 'Night Life', 'Then take a long walk at the Longhua Memorial Park of Revolutionary Martyrs. A memorial park built in 1981 to commemorate the communists who was executed between 1927 to 1931 when the ground it is on now was the Garrison Command and prison. Then head to dinner. Food dumplings galore – I was enticed to try this place as they serve soup dumplings the size of my face and it was decent for its p', 'Beijing', 'img/countries/China/img-1.jpg', NULL, 'Beijing, China\'\'s sprawling capital, has history stretching back 3 millennia. Yet it\'\'s known as much for modern architecture as its ancient sites such as the grand Forbidden City complex, the imperial palace during the Ming and Qing dynasties. Nearby, the massive Tiananmen Square pedestrian plaza is the site of Mao Zedong\'\'s mausoleum and the National Museum of China, displaying a vast collection of cultural relics.', 988);
